enhanced_by.reason: Both methods manipulate JSON objects, making it easier to set up a test scenario with a populated JSON object.
The buildJSONString method can be used to create a JSONObject that can be passed to sortJSONObject, facilitating test setup.
The pullValue method can be used to verify the sorted order of keys in the returned Map from sortJSONObject.
The getJSONStringValue method can be used to verify specific values in the sorted Map, ensuring they match the expected values.
